Logical Operators

1) And - &&
2) OR - ||
3) NOT - !

* Logical operators works only with Boolean data types
* Logical operators will be used to combine multiple conditions

==> Table for AND operator (&&)

    | value 1 && value2 = Result |
    | true && true = true |
    | true && false = false |
    | false && true = false |
    | false && false = false |

    In Java, if the first value is true, Java will check the other queries.
    However, if the first value is false, Java will ignore everything afterwards


==> Table for OR operator ( || )

     value1 || value2 = Result
     true || true =true
     true || false = true
     false || true = true
     false || false = false

 ==> table for NOT operator (!)
 ===============================

 value = Result
 !true = false
 !false = true

